{
  "doc_id": "17954",
  "text": "Sentinel-2 images were downloaded from the Copernicus Open Access Hub for the area of municipalities Novi Bečej and Žabalj in 2016. Sentinel-2 satellites use MSI sensor that measures reflected energy in 13 spectral bands with a spatial resolution of 10, 20 and 60 meters [CITATION_1] . The images were atmospherically corrected in Sen2Cor software in order to get the true reflection value from the ground. A dark object subtraction method is used, which assumes that the pixel with the lowest value in each band should be equal to zero, and that its radiometric value is actually the result of aggregate atmospheric errors [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . B2 (Blue), B3 (Green), B4 (Red) and B8 (NIR) bands were selected and merged into one raster. The images were cut to the shape of municipalities. ",
